@page "/"

<PageTitle>QueryLantern</PageTitle>

<div class="hero">
    <h1>QueryLantern</h1>
    <p class="lead">A local-first, conversational SQL analyst. Ask questions in plain language, get SQL,
        run governed queries on your own databases, and review every change before it happens.</p>

    <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="connections">Set up a connection</a>
        <a class="btn btn-outline-secondary" href="chat">Open the chat</a>
    </div>

    <div class="features">
        <div class="feature">
            <h3>Local-first</h3>
            <p>Your credentials, catalog, and activity journal never leave your machine unless you choose to connect to a remote model.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature">
            <h3>Governed queries</h3>
            <p>Reads run automatically. Writes are staged and require your explicit approval before a single row changes.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature">
            <h3>Many engines</h3>
            <p>SQLite, PostgreSQL, MySQL, SQL Server, Oracle, DuckDB, ClickHouse, and ODBC — one agent for all of them.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<style>
    .hero {
        max-width: 920px;
        margin: 2rem auto;
    }
    .hero h1 {
        font-size: 2.6rem;
        font-weight: 700;
    }
    .lead {
        color: var(--ql-muted);
        font-size: 1.05rem;
    }
    .hero-actions {
        display: flex;
        gap: 0.75rem;
        margin: 1.5rem 0 2.5rem;
    }
    .features {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
        gap: 1rem;
    }
    .feature {
        background: var(--ql-panel);
        border: 1px solid var(--ql-border);
        border-radius: 10px;
        padding: 1.1rem 1.2rem;
    }
    .feature h3 {
        margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
        color: var(--ql-accent-2);
    }
    .feature p {
        color: var(--ql-muted);
        margin: 0;
    }
    .btn-outline-secondary {
        color: var(--ql-text);
        border-color: var(--ql-border);
    }
</style>
